{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"alias":"irongray-profound-abalone","description":"The review-bot's structured operational logs (the `_emit()` INFO events â€”\n`voter_voted`, `voter_skip`, `merge_detection`, and all `reconcile_*`) are silently\ndropped in production, so operators are blind to what the bot decides. Configure a\nlogging handler for rebar's loggers so these reach stdout/journald.\n\n## Why\n`src/rebar/review_bot/` contains NO logging setup (`grep` for `basicConfig`/`dictConfig`\nin `src/rebar/` returns nothing). The container runs `uvicorn rebar.review_bot.app:app`;\nuvicorn configures only its own `uvicorn.*` loggers and never the root or `rebar.*`\nloggers. So a `logging.getLogger(\"rebar.review_bot.voter\").info(...)` record has no\nhandler and falls through to Python's `logging.lastResort`, which emits **WARNING and\nabove only** â€” every INFO `_emit` line is discarded. This was directly observed during\nincident triage: `journalctl` showed uvicorn's own access lines and the `print()`-to-stderr\nmarkers (`VOTER_ERROR`, `ARTIFACT_EMIT_ERROR`) but ZERO `voter_voted`/`reconcile_*` lines,\nmaking a healthy-but-slow reconciler look dead. The `_emit` docstrings call these\n\"observability markers\" â€” dropping them violates that documented intent.\n\n## What\nAdd a `_configure_logging()` to `src/rebar/review_bot/app.py`, called once at module import\n(before `app = FastAPI(...)`), that attaches a `StreamHandler(sys.stdout)` to the `rebar`\nlogger at level `INFO` (overridable via a `REVIEW_BOT_LOG_LEVEL` env var), with a bare\n`\"%(message)s\"` formatter (the `_emit` payload is already JSON), an idempotency marker on the\nhandler (so repeated imports/reloads don't stack handlers), and `propagate=False` (so records\ndo NOT double-log through uvicorn/root). Targeting the `rebar` logger specifically â€” not root\nâ€” avoids duplicating uvicorn's access logs.\n\n## Scope\n- `src/rebar/review_bot/app.py`: add `_configure_logging()` + `import sys`; call at import.\n- `tests/unit/test_review_bot.py`: add a test asserting a `rebar.review_bot.*` INFO record\n  reaches stdout after the app module configures logging (RED before the fix).\n- Non-goal (separate follow-up): shipping logs to a shared service (CloudWatch Logs group).\n  This change makes the logs *emitted*; centralizing them is tracked separately.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] A `logging.getLogger(\"rebar.review_bot.voter\").info(...)` record is written to stdout\n      once the review-bot app module has configured logging; before the fix the same record\n      produces no stdout output (proving the drop).\n      Proving command: `python -m pytest tests/unit/test_review_bot.py -k configure_logging -q`\n      passes, and the test is confirmed RED on the pre-fix tree.\n- [ ] The handler is idempotent: importing/configuring twice does not attach a second handler\n      (no duplicate log lines).\n      Proving command: assert `len([h for h in logging.getLogger(\"rebar\").handlers if marker])\n      == 1` after two `_configure_logging()` calls (in the test).\n- [ ] `REVIEW_BOT_LOG_LEVEL=DEBUG` lowers the effective level (env override honored); an\n      absent/invalid value falls back to INFO.\n      Proving command: covered by a parametrized assertion in the test.\n- [ ] Existing gates stay green.\n      Proving command: `make lint && make typecheck && python -m pytest tests/unit/test_review_bot.py -q` all exit 0.","id":"c130-6a87-531e-4441","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"review-bot: configure logging so structured _emit INFO events reach stdout/journald"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784158135764175001,"uuid":"b7b1ef98-f08b-43c1-b460-5d4fed215618"}